This repository contains simple explanations
of basic programming concepts in python 
VARIABLES 
  it is used to store values 

x = 10
name = "Python"

LOOPS
  Loops are used to repeat a block of code.

for i in range(5):
    print(i)

OPERATIONS 
  Operators are used to perform operations on variables.
Types of operators:
Arithmetic: +, -, *, /
Comparison: ==, !=, >
Logical: and, or, not
CONDITIONAL STATEMENTS
  Used to make decisions in a program.

age = 18
if age >= 18:
    print("You are eligible to vote")
else:
    print("Not eligible")
